<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head') %>
  <title>PictoCard – Privacy Policy</title>
</head>
<body>
<%- include('partials/header') %>

<main class="container container-narrow prose">

  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="updated">Last updated: <%= lastUpdated %></p>

  <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    PictoCard is designed to minimise data collection. We do <strong>not</strong> store any emails,
    uploaded images, or personal information on our servers after your session ends.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Session Data</h2>
  <p>
    During the card-creation flow we temporarily hold the following in your browser session (server-side,
    in memory only):
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your name and email address (for verification)</li>
    <li>The recipient's email or Discord username</li>
    <li>The uploaded image and card text</li>
    <li>The generated card image</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This data is automatically discarded once the card is sent or the server restarts. It is never
    written to disk or a database.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Email Delivery</h2>
  <p>
    Emails are sent via a third-party SMTP provider. The provider may retain delivery logs in accordance
    with their own privacy policy. We send a verification code to the sender and the finished card to
    the recipient - no further email marketing is conducted.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Opt-out List</h2>
  <p>
    If you opt out via the <a href="/optout">opt-out page</a> your email address is added to an
    in-memory list that prevents cards from being sent to you. This list is also cleared on server
    restart and is never persisted.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Discord</h2>
  <p>
    If you connect your Discord account, we receive your Discord username and ID temporarily for the
    purpose of sending a card. No Discord data is stored beyond the current session.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    We use a single session cookie to track the card-creation flow. No advertising or tracking
    cookies are used.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy-related enquiries please open an issue on our
    <a href="https://github.com/larsenv/pictocard" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub repository</a>.
  </p>

</main>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
